 this species during daytime searches, and it was the least common mist net capture. We documented 65 Pteropus food plants in our study area. Nyctimene sanctacrucis was not detected on Nendo\u00a8, Tinakula and Reef Islands despite considerable effort. We consider this bat is likely extinct, if in fact it is a distinct species.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Lavery, Tyrone H.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leary, Tanya N.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Shaw, Christina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tahi, Martika", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Posala, Corzzierrah", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pierce, Ray", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/48c662b56fb422b6292c708bc664bd0e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/edf07265a8e05edff91dbf0eff178f2c773c66ac96be688cf68ca0391ef25a69", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/DPERA3G2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/DPERA3G2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/57bce583d79caf6a14fe8414bb62c288!/b71597-74155", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "27", "title": "Pacific Conservation Biology", "volume": "27"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://m